name: ARROWROOT (aka ARROWROOT FLOUR, POWDER, or STARCH)
dishes: baked goods, e.g., biscuits, breads, cakes, cookies, muffins, pies, scones

matches.name: What it is: a thickening agent, less processed than cornstarch, made from the
arrowroot plant (a tuber grown in the tropics)
Tips: Dissolve in a little cold water before adding to sauces; or dissolve
about one tablespoon of powder per cup of cold liquid before bringing it to a
simmer. It becomes clear as it cooks. Stir constantly, do not overheat, which makes arrowroot lose its thickening power.
Brand: Authentic Foods, Bob’s Red Mill
Possible substitutes: cornstarch, flour, kuzu, tapioca starch
